snippet: Texas A&M quarterback Johnny Manziel, a redshirt freshman, did not ruin No. 1 Alabama’s hopes of repeating as national champion by himself, but he was a big part of the Aggies’ upset win Saturday.
abstract: Texas A&M upsets No. 1 Alabama, 29-24, in college football; A&M quarterback Johnny Manziel, redshirt freshman, completes 24 of 31 passes for 253 yards with no interceptions.
lead_paragraph: Texas A&M quarterback Johnny Manziel, a redshirt freshman, did not ruin No. 1 Alabama’s hopes of repeating as national champion by himself, but he was a big part of the Aggies’ upset win Saturday.

headline.seo: Error-Prone Alabama Falls to Texas A&M
headline.main: Error-Prone Alabama Seals Its Loss and, Maybe, Its Fate
headline.print_headline: Error-Prone Alabama Seals Its Loss and, Maybe, Its Fate
